org.spongepowered.api.data.value

Interface ValueFactory.BoundedValueBuilder<E>

  • Type Parameters:
    E - The type of element
    Enclosing interface:
    ValueFactory

    public static interface ValueFactory.BoundedValueBuilder<E>
    A builder pattern for constructing MutableBoundedValues without the hassle of keeping track of the order of arguments.

    • Method Detail

      • comparator

        ValueFactory.BoundedValueBuilder<E> comparator(Comparator<E> comparator)
        If E is not Comparable, a Comparator is required. The builder by default will attempt to check if the type is a Comparable and delegate to the default Comparable.compareTo(Object) for comparisons. In short, the Comparator is only required if the element is not Comparable, or custom comparisons are required.
        Parameters:
        comparator - The comparator to use
        Returns:
        This builder, for chaining

      • defaultValue

        ValueFactory.BoundedValueBuilder<E> defaultValue(E defaultValue)
        Sets the default value. This is required. If no value is set, the default value transitively sets the value.
        Parameters:
        defaultValue - The default value
        Returns:
        This builder, for chaining

      • actualValue

        ValueFactory.BoundedValueBuilder<E> actualValue(E actual)
        Sets the actual value. Though not required, if the value is different from the defaultValue(Object), it should be set.
        Parameters:
        actual - The actual value
        Returns:
        This builder, for chaining

      • build

        MutableBoundedValue<E> build()
        Builds a new MutableBoundedValue. The requirements are that the minimum(Object), maximum(Object), defaultValue(Object) are set, and if the E is not Comparable, comparator(Comparator) is set.
        Returns:
        The newly constructed value
